FWIW Zag, VTMB never even hiccuped as far as sound goes with my AC97 on
board sound, but it's an ASUS K8V-SE Deluxe mobo, not an nForce chipset
of any kind, so perhaps Intel are the culprits...? I've been using it
for 2.5yrs now, predominately with headphones, but compared to my
previous rig the sound is fantastic (even has decent 5.1 with my
Logitech speakers though I haven't plugged in the rear speakers since
the move). I don't need to ask you if all your mobo &amp; sounds card
drivers are up to date, do I? ;-p Also, mine is running on WinXP Pro SP2
&amp; has since I installed VTMB - frankly, I'm surprised you're still
bothering with Win98 - is this mainly what you're running VTMB on? If
so, try it on XP &amp; tick Win98 compatibility mode to get around some
other early engine bugs (not sure if it still applies to v1.2). Luck!

